Fix event wildcard tap pattern matching

DESCRIPTION:
Tap pattern `*:compute -> *` (match all compute events across modules)
does not match any events. No tap calls are inserted into the AST.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. Tap pattern `*:compute` correctly matches events named "compute" in any module
2. Logger tap fires for compute() call
3. Test passes with output: "[TAP] input:compute\n"

ROOT CAUSE:
Likely issue in taps.kz pathMatches() function (around line 114) or
in the wildcard path handling. The pattern "*:compute" should:
1. Extract module="*" (wildcard) and path="compute"
2. Match invocations where path matches "compute"
3. Ignore module (match any module since * is wildcard)

RELATED:
- See also: 510_070 (metatype binding), 510_071 (module wildcard patterns)
